Preheat your #oven to 200°C. Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into four long strips then chop widthways into roughly 2cm pieces. Pop the aubergine chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and sprinkle over the @North Indian style spice mix{1}. Toss to coat, then arrange in a single layer. Roast the aubergine until golden brown and soft, ~{25-30%minutes}, turning halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces. Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #saucepan over medium-high heat. Once hot, add the onion and @diced chicken breast{260%g}, cook, stirring, until softened and turning brown, ~{5-6%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling chicken and its packaging. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Add the @korma curry paste{50%g} and cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}. Add the @tomato passata{1}, @red split lentils{100%g}, @water{350%ml}(for the lentils), @vegetable stock paste{10} and @sugar{1/2}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and bring to a boil. Once boiling, lower the heat to medium and cook until the lentils are soft, ~{20-25%minutes}. Stir regularly to make sure it doesn't stick to the bottom of the pan and add a splash of water if it is starting to get too thick.

Meanwhile, pour the @water{300%ml}(for the rice) into a #saucepan and bring to the boil. When boiling, add @salt{1/4%tsp}, stir in the @basmati rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Roughly chop the @coriander{1} (stalks and all). Once the lentils are cooked, add the @baby spinach{100%g} a handful at a time, stirring, until wilted and piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir through half the roasted aubergine, half the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g} and half the coriander. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Once everything is ready, divide the rice between plates. Top with the dal, add the remaining roasted aubergine and remaining yoghurt. Scatter over the remaining coriander. Enjoy!

> MOD Step 2: If you've decided to add chicken to your meal, cook the chicken with the onions and carry on with the rest of the recipe as instructed. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling chicken and its packaging. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.